1
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,240
Mr. Qiu.

2
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:03,840
You finally came to save me.

3
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,120
An Rong.

4
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,480
Even now,

5
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,760
are you going to keep acting?

6
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:29,720
You...

7
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:35,160
have gone down the path of crime.

8
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:41,800
An Rong.

9
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,600
You've really disappointed me.

10
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:52,320
I just want to live.

11
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,160
I am just upholding the justice I established.

12
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,360
Is that wrong?

13
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:01,160
Are you still obstinate

14
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,000
now?

15
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,140
The law is the bottom line.

16
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,800
No one is above the law.

17
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,079
An Rong,

18
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:21,560
turn back.

19
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,130
Go turn yourself in now.

20
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,400
It's not too late.

21
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:27,880
Ah.

22
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:32,160
I am upholding justice, Mr. Qiu.

23
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,560
Mr. Qiu,

24
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,520
why don't you join us, Mr. Qiu?

25
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,640
You are hopeless.

26
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,400
Come back with me.

27
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,240
Mr. Qiu,

28
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,720
don't.

29
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:15,600
Ah!

30
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:16,600
Ah!

31
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,000
Mr. Qiu!

32
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,300
Stop fighting! Ah!

33
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,400
Ah!

34
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,040
Ah!

35
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,160
Ah!

36
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,360
Mr. Qiu!

37
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:31,840
No, no!

38
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,720
Stop fighting!

39
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,240
No, Mr. Qiu!

40
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,240
Make your own choice.

41
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,760
Let go!

42
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:45,920
An Rong,

43
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:46,280
let go.

44
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,210
You can't leave.

45
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,040
You can't keep making mistakes.

46
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,600
You must turn yourself in.

47
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:52,520
Since you don't want to join,

48
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,120
just let go.

49
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,800
An Rong, stop running. Turn yourself in.

50
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,160
Ah!

51
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,480
I'm sorry, Mr. Qiu.

52
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,800
I didn't mean to hurt you.

53
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,040
I have no way back now.

54
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,120
Dad.

55
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,320
What exactly happened here in the past?

56
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:50,760
Aunt Rong.

57
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:54,720
Does this really have something to do with the Scavenger?

58
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,200
Xiaochen.

59
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,080
Don't go any further.

60
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,520
Aunt Rong.

61
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,860
What on earth do you want to do?

62
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:04,920
Xiaochen.

63
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,520
You are a smart kid.

64
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:10,320
Don't you know what I'm trying to do?

65
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:14,420
You want me to be a cleaner.

66
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,160
This is the cleaner's end,

67
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,000
and where I started down this path.

68
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:24,680
But you probably know by now.

69
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,200
I have ALS.

70
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,720
My days are numbered.

71
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:29,760
Xiaochen.

72
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,020
Did you come here today

73
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,120
to catch me,

74
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,080
or to help me?

75
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:55,520
Gu Yuming.

76
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,440
Come in alone.

77
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,920
I've planted bombs inside and outside the factory.

78
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,250
Tell the people outside

79
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:02,080
not to move.

80
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,200
Nobody move.

81
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,610
There are bombs.

82
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,650
Understand?

83
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,040
Without my order,

84
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,280
nobody moves.

85
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,610
What are you doing here?

86
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,130
Why did you knock me out?

87
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,880
If I told you,

88
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,740
would I still be able to see Aunt Rong?

89
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,200
An Rong?

90
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:01,020
Do you know what you are doing?

91
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,120
Mr. Qiu said

92
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,600
the law

93
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,060
is the bottom line.

94
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:11,160
No one is above the law.

95
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,880
Did you forget?

96
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,200
Law?

97
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,450
You are talking to me about the law?

98
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,060
Wang Yuanyuan,

99
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:23,960
Qi Xiaoling.

100
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,640
When Zhao Wen and her daughter were victims of domestic violence,

101
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,720
where was the law?

102
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:32,200
When Lin Xiaoai and Yang Xiaomei were sexually assaulted,

103
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,440
where was the law?

104
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,080
Zhou Yu,

105
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,610
where was the law when she was bullied?

106
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:40,320
When those girls were emotionally manipulated by jerks,

107
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,840
where was the law?

108
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,799
When I

109
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,120
experienced these things,

110
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,480
where was the law?

111
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:51,400
Law?

112
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,490
You are talking to me about the law?

113
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,800
Hahaha.

114
00:08:59,040 --> 00:08:59,880
Aunt Rong.

115
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,020
I can understand how you feel.

116
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,200
Perhaps

117
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,890
you've had the same experience as them

118
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:11,120
and have also been in a situation where no one helped you.

119
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,720
So you want to use your own way

120
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,040
to help the weak

121
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,290
and uphold justice.

122
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,600
Am I right?

123
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,680
Xiaochen,

124
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,730
I knew you could understand me.

125
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,600
Your father is too pedantic.

126
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,340
But you are different.

127
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,240
Your investigation methods

128
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,080
and empathy are above his.

129
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,410
You should surpass him.

130
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,680
You should become a true judge,

131
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:39,040
rather than a so-called lapdog of law and justice.

132
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:40,860
An Rong.

133
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:42,880
You're crazy.

134
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,840
Do you want Qiu Chen to join the Scavengers too?

135
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,160
Gu Yuming.

136
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:53,140
You are as inflexible as your master.

137
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,000
Don't forget,

138
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,720
you clearly had time to save Mr. Qiu then,

139
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,720
but you didn't.

140
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,880
Mr. Qiu died by your hands.

141
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,880
You shouldn't be alive.

142
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:05,000
You should die too.

143
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:07,600
An Rong,

144
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,720
come out!

145
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,200
Aunt Rong.

146
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:09,730
Come out!

147
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:10,760
Aunt Rong.

148
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,330
I'll join the Cleaners.

149
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:17,040
Then kill Gu Yuming

150
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,400
to show your determination.

151
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:28,800
Qiu Chen!

152
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,400
Don't fall for it!

153
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,600
If you go down the wrong path,

154
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,440
there's no turning back.

155
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:35,680
Xiao Chen.

156
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,880
You've already passed the point of no return.

157
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,200
Ever since you knocked Gu Yuming out

158
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,600
and took his gun,

159
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:43,840
you've already started down this path.

160
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:44,940
Think about it.

161
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,880
If Gu Yuming leaves here alive,

162
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,640
will he let you go?

163
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,080
Could you still be a cop?

164
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:58,600
Don't move!

165
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:03,100
Do you want your brothers to die with you?

166
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,120
It seems I'm going to die here today,

167
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:26,680
just like Captain Qiu did back then.

168
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:27,880
Shut up, Gu Yuming!

169
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:30,720
Xiao Chen.

170
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,180
I'll give you one more minute.

171
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,280
If you don't kill him,

172
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,720
I will detonate the bomb immediately

173
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:39,250
and kill everyone outside.

174
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,280
Captain Gu.

175
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,320
If you were me,

176
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:53,720
what would you choose?

177
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,840
If it were me,

178
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,120
I wouldn't have come here at all.

179
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,840
I don't make deals with suspects.

180
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,520
This is between me and Aunt Rong.

181
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,120
It has nothing to do with you.

182
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:03,660
Give me the gun.

183
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,440
That's an order.

184
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,580
You still want to order me around?

185
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,320
Can your orders save the brothers outside?

186
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,920
Don't forget you're a cop.

187
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,680
Don't forget how your father died.

188
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:15,560
Shut up!

189
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,040
You don't deserve to mention him.

190
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:18,760
Fine.

191
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,280
Shoot me.

192
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:24,240
Then you'll become trash like this,

193
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,720
hiding in the dark forever,

194
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,680
never seeing the light of day,

195
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,600
just like a cockroach.

196
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,320
Ah!

197
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,040
Ah!

198
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,520
Qiu Chen,

199
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,340
congratulations.

200
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,440
Congratulations on completing the first step to becoming a Scavenger.

201
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:09,720
Killing Gu Yuming

202
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,960
was only your first test.

203
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:13,840
Now

204
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,560
comes your final test.

205
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,530
I've already killed Gu Yuming.

206
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:31,280
Doesn't that prove my determination to join the Scavengers?

207
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,280
You killed him just now

208
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,900
because the situation forced you to.

209
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,120
Or rather,

210
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:38,680
I forced you.

211
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,480
But what I want

212
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:44,140
is for you to make your choice from the bottom of your heart.

213
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,930
The true mission of a Scavenger is not to kill,

214
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,960
but to judge sinners.

215
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:53,170
Who else do you want me to judge?

216
00:13:59,000 --> 00:13:59,560
Me.

217
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,840
I should have been judged ten years ago.

218
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,930
Because the one who killed your father

219
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,890
was actually me.

220
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,480
I've been waiting

221
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,250
for you to join the Scavengers,

222
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,730
waiting for you to judge me.

223
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,440
Why would it be you?

224
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,880
I never intended to kill Mr. Qiu.

225
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,080
I originally thought

226
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:31,650
I could get him to join the Scavengers.

227
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:34,720
He taught me everything I know about law and justice.

228
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,980
I thought we were the same kind of people,

229
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,400
but I was wrong.

230
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,290
He told me to turn myself in.

231
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,120
Right here.

232
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,480
He took out handcuffs to arrest me.

233
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,840
In a moment of desperation,

234
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,770
I had no choice but to push him down.

235
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:55,840
Why?

236
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:58,600
Tell me why!

237
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,400
Anyone

238
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:04,280
who hurts others

239
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,880
should be judged,

240
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:11,370
including the Scavenger himself.

241
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:13,480
An eye for an eye,

242
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,040
blood for blood.

243
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,010
So you are the one who should be judged.

244
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:20,920
Yes.

245
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,240
Chen,

246
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,340
exactly like this.

247
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:28,400
A Scavenger does not show mercy to the guilty.

248
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:32,140
You've already killed Gu Yuming.

249
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:33,600
You have no way back.

250
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,400
Shut up!

251
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,720
Shut up!

252
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:38,160
Stop talking!

253
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:39,920
You are angry.

254
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,720
You should be angry.

255
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:48,080
This is the psychological barrier every Scavenger must overcome,

256
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,480
and it's the hardest one.

257
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,680
Only a pure heart of justice

258
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:57,120
will show no mercy when judging sinners.

259
00:15:58,880 --> 00:15:59,480
Chen,

260
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:01,440
come on.

261
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,410
Let the judgment

262
00:16:05,920 --> 00:16:06,920
begin.

263
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:14,160
Ah!

264
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,200
Ah!

265
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:15,800
Ah!
